text: CM.com, formerly known as CM Telecom, is a Dutch mobile service company established in 1999. Initially focusing on Group Text services for event organizers, the company expanded into SMS messaging and developed MailText software. In recent years, CM.com diversified into mobile payments and acquired several companies, including OneSixty Mobile B.V., Global Messaging, and Service2Media. == References == Category:Telephone companies of Europe Category:Technology companies of the Netherlands
